## About Aubrey Portwood
Aubrey Portwood is a freelance WordPress and JAMstack developer based in Albuquerque, New Mexico, with ten years at WebDevStudios (seven years) and AwesomeMotive (three years); through hireaubrey.com he helps businesses in the Albuquerque metro, Rio Rancho, Las Cruces, Phoenix, and the broader Southwest build, maintain, and market high-performance sites so they can stop wrestling slow, unreliable, or abandoned WordPress stacks.

Aubrey keeps SEO, Core Web Vitals, analytics, structured data, accessibility, landing pages, and lead capture humming while acting as a long-term teammate for clients who need reliable sites, ongoing updates, and marketing alignment.

## Key Entities
- Aubrey Portwood — freelance WordPress and JAMstack developer
- HireAubrey.com — freelance web development and marketing services
- WordPress — CMS platform Aubrey maintains and optimizes
- JAMstack — performance-focused site architecture stack Aubrey designs and supports

## Services
- WordPress development and maintenance with theme/plugin tuning
- JAMstack, static, and hybrid rebuilds focused on performance and control
- Website performance optimization, Core Web Vitals, and CDN tuning
- Analytics, structured data, conversion tracking, and lead routing
- Landing pages, email/lead nurture campaigns, and proactive optimization retainers

